# FA copyrighted game content — NEVER commit.
# Extension list cross-checked against fighters-codex docs/fa/formats/.
# Both cases listed: gitignore patterns are case-sensitive on Linux, and FA
# files copied from an install vary in case.
# Archives
*.LIB
# (lowercase *.lib is already ignored above as an MSVC artifact)
# Images and palettes
*.PIC
*.pic
*.PAL
*.pal
*.RAW
*.raw
# 3D models and terrain
*.SH
*.sh
*.T2
*.t2
# Missions and maps
*.M
*.m
*.MM
*.mm
# Type/stat records (BRF DSL)
*.PT
*.pt
*.OT
*.ot
*.NT
*.nt
*.JT
*.jt
*.SEE
*.see
*.ECM
*.ecm
*.GAS
*.gas
*.BRF
*.brf
# Audio
*.11K
*.11k
*.8K
*.8k
*.5K
*.5k
*.22K
*.22k
*.XMI
*.xmi
*.MUS
*.mus
# Video and cutscenes
*.CB8
*.cb8
*.SEQ
*.seq
*.VDO
*.vdo
*.FBC
*.fbc
# Campaign and briefings
*.CAM
*.cam
*.MC
*.mc
*.MT
*.mt
# UI, fonts, and overlays
*.INF
*.inf
*.LAY
*.lay
*.HUD
*.hud
*.FNT
*.fnt
*.DLG
*.dlg
*.MNU
*.mnu
*.PTS
*.pts
*.HGR
*.hgr
# Pilots, AI, and symbols
*.P
*.p
*.PLT
*.plt
*.AI
*.ai
*.BI
*.bi
*.SMS
*.sms
# Installer
*.SSF
*.ssf
*.RGN
*.rgn
# FA also ships files with generic extensions (.TXT, .BIN, .DAT, .CFG) that
# cannot be safely blanket-ignored (e.g. CMakeLists.txt). Never commit those
# either — reviewers must catch them.
